'''VirtualBox''' is a free [[x86 virtualization]] software package, originally created by [[Germany|German]] software company innotek, now developed by [[Sun Microsystems]] as part of its [[Sun xVM]] virtualization platform. It is installed on an existing host operating system; within this application, additional operating systems, each known as a ''Guest OS'', can be loaded and run, each with its own virtual environment.
Supported host operating systems include [[Linux]], [[Mac OS X]], [[OS/2 Warp]], Windows [[Microsoft Windows XP|XP]] or [[Windows Vista|Vista]], and [[Solaris_(operating_system)|Solaris]], while supported guest operating systems include [[FreeBSD]], Linux, [[OpenBSD]], OS/2 Warp, Windows and Solaris.<ref>[http://www.virtualbox.org/wiki/Guest_OSes "Status: Guest OSes" page on VirtualBox website]</ref>
